name: Alaina Castillo
description: '''Alaina Castillo''' (born November 16, 1999) is an American musician. Born in Houston, Texas, Castillo began to post ASMR-inspired covers of songs on her YouTube channel during her freshman year of high school, and released her first original song in 2018. She has since released six [[Extended play|extended plays]], and has performed at the [[Latin American Music Awards of 2021|2021 Latin American Music Awards]] and [[Coachella 2022]]. She was the first musician to be featured in the US iteration of RADAR, an artist development program headed by [[Spotify]], and the staff of ''Billboard'' called Castillo a "Latin Artist to Watch" in 2021.
